ferences, weight by treated counts, and use sum_h w_h"'^2*(s1_h''^2/n1_h+s0_h''^2/n0_h) for a Neyman-style fixed-strata variance; fail clearly if any stratum lacks either arm. Produce a specification data frame containing naive plus all eight adjusted rows, estimate, standard error, 95% lower/upper, benchmark, gap=estimate-benchmark, covariates, support, estimator, and retained treated/control N. Figure must show all nine observational estimates with 95% intervals and benchmark as horizontal line; Okabe-Ito palette/theme constants at top of script, caption not title, zero-line if useful, 300+ dpi, exactly one PNG at figures/spec-curve.png. Table must include all nine rows, dollars sensibly rounded, benchmark/gap, intervals and sample counts. Memo around 450 words must adjudicate based strictly on computed curve and distinguish robust recovery, favorable-specification-only recovery, or absent recovery; concede conditional ignorability/unobserved confounding and common-support target changes. Constraints: set.seed before anything stochastic; self-contained Rscript recreates all outputs; no web; no package installation; no extra figures; do not edit BRIEF.md, sol-session.log, routing-log.md, or terra logs; no commits. Acceptance checks: Rscript script.R exits 0 from current directory; benchmark recomputed near 1794 but not hard-coded; 9 rows exactly; all 8 factorial cells present; figure PNG 300+ dpi and no in-plot title; memo 400-525 words and claims match numbers. Return format in the log: conclusion, evidence, changed files, residual risk, and tokens used.'"' < /dev/null > terra-implementation.log 2>&1" in ~/Documents/github/resources/ai-for-research/demos/orchestration-lab/runs/46-sol/vhigh-lalonde
