ffort=low` for purely mechanical edits;\012     use `--model gpt-5.6-luna` for the cheapest fully-specified bulk.\012   - These write into the current directory — give concurrent one-shots\012     **disjoint output paths** and never overlap their write scope.\012   - They are fire-and-forget: background several and read their `.log` files\012     back. After each returns, **open its artifact and verify it yourself** —\012     treat Terra's output as untrusted until you've checked it against the\012     brief. A Terra one-shot is the weaker model; if its result looks wrong,\012     fix it in your own reasoning, don't defer to it.\012\0123. **Use `spawn_agent` sparingly.** Under a Sol lead every spawned child is\012   *also Sol-priced* (subagents inherit the lead's model and effort — there is\012   no per-agent override). Only spawn when a one-shot can't give you what you\012   need: a live back-and-forth, context isolation, or a blind same-tier\012   resample on a high-stakes call. For ordinary bulk, prefer the out-of-band\012   Terra one-shot above.\012\0124. **Respect the brief's constraints exactly** — including "at most one\012   revision cycle," "at most 3 delegations," "do not fetch anything from the\012   web," and "do not install packages." A Terra out-of-band one-shot counts as\012   one delegation.\012\012**Write your results to the current working directory:**\012\012- **The deliverables named in `./BRIEF.md`** (e.g. `script.R`, `summary.md` /\012  `report.md` / `memo.md`, `figures/…`, any table the brief asks for). Follow\012  the brief's figure conventions (Okabe-Ito palette, caption-not-title,\012  300+ dpi, reference levels at zero where applicable).\012\012- **`routing-log.md`** — the record of how you led. Include:\012  - **Route table:** one row per workstream — *what it was*, *owner*\012    (`Sol (lead, direct)` / `Terra out-of-band` / `Sol spawn`), *why that\012    owner*, and *acceptance check*.\012  - **Out-of-band calls:** for each Terra/Luna one-shot, the **exact command**\012    you ran and the **`tokens used: N`** it reported (copy the number from its\012    `.log`).\012  - **What you reasoned directly:** a short note on the analytical decisions\012    you kept in the lead (this is the point of a Sol lead — make it visible).\012  - **Friction:** anything that failed, any sandbox/stdin gotcha, any Terra\012    output you had to correct.\012  - **Token total:** a final line\012    `[SOL LEAD TOKENS: ____]  + Terra one-shots: <sum>  = <total>`\012    — leave the SOL LEAD TOKENS blank for the operator to fill from the Codex\012    status line; you fill the Terra sum from the `.log` files.\012\012- Do **not** write outside this directory. Do **not** commit, push, or touch\012  anything in `runs/` other than the current leaf.\012\012When everything the brief asks for exists and you've verified it against the\012brief, give a one-paragraph completion summary: what you produced, what you\012delegated to Terra vs. reasoned yourself, and any residual risk.
