+# Routing log
+
+## Route table
+
+| Workstream | Owner | Why this owner | Acceptance check |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| Estimand, specification grid, trimming, and inference design | Sol (lead, direct) | These are the compact, consequential methods judgments that determine what the curve means. | ATT target and any support-induced target change are explicit; the grid varies both requested axes; no ordinary bootstrap is used for 1-NN. |
+| Mechanical implementation and first-pass rendering | Terra out-of-band | The analytical contract was fixed, leaving bounded R implementation and rendering with objective checks. | `Rscript script.R` exits 0; nine rows cover naive plus the full 2×2×2 grid; all requested artifacts exist. |
+| Analytical integration and adjudication | Sol (lead, direct) | Interpretation of specification dependence and permissible claims remains lead-owned. | Memo claims follow the complete curve, distinguish conditioning from identification, and avoid unqualified success/failure claims. |
+| Independent artifact audit | Terra out-of-band | A bounded read-only verification pass could challenge arithmetic, implementation, and deliverable compliance cheaply. | Each artifact receives PASS/FAIL evidence; no files are changed. |
+| Revision, final rerun, and routing record | Sol (lead, direct) | The lead must adjudicate worker findings and own the final integrated state. | One revision cycle only; 320-dpi metadata verified; final script rerun and static checks pass. |
+
+No Sol-priced `spawn_agent` child was used.
+
+## Out-of-band calls
+
+### 1. Terra implementation — tokens used: 120,457
+
+```bash
+codex exec --model gpt-5.6-terra -c model_reasoning_effort=medium --sandbox workspace-write --skip-git-repo-check -C "$PWD" 'Objective: Mechanically implement the fixed LaLonde specification-curve analysis and create first-pass deliverables. Inputs and authoritative paths: ./BRIEF.md; installed R packages causaldata, MatchIt, sandwich, lmtest, estimatr; current directory only. In scope: create ./script.R, ./spec-table.md, ./memo.md, and ./figures/spec-curve.png. Fixed analysis contract: load nsw_mixtape and cps_mixtape; benchmark is unadjusted NSW treated minus NSW experimental control mean re78. Observational composite is 185 NSW treated plus all 15,992 CPS controls. Include naive composite difference with a Welch 95% CI. Run exactly eight adjusted specifications crossing covariates {demographics: age educ black hisp marr nodegree; demographics plus earnings: those plus re74 re75}, support {untrimmed; trimmed to intersection of treated and control fitted propensity-score ranges}, and estimator {1-nearest-neighbor propensity-score matching with replacement targeting ATT; five-stratum propensity-score subclassification using quintiles of treated scores and ATT weights}. Fit a main-effects logit separately for each covariate set on the full composite. For trimming, use the intersection of full-sample fitted-score ranges, disclose the retained treated count, and use the already-fitted scores rather than silently redefining support. For 1-NN, MatchIt is allowed with estimand=ATT, replace=TRUE, distance supplied from the fixed logit; calculate treated-minus-matched-control pair differences. Use a control-reuse cluster-robust intercept-only variance for pair differences (finite-sample CR1 based on clusters defined by matched original control ID), not an ordinary bootstrap; code and label this transparently as an approximate matching interval conditional on fitted scores. For stratification, cut by unique treated-score quintiles, estimate within-stratum differences, weight by treated counts, and use sum_h w_h^2*(s1_h^2/n1_h+s0_h^2/n0_h) for a Neyman-style fixed-strata variance; fail clearly if any stratum lacks either arm. Produce a specification data frame containing naive plus all eight adjusted rows, estimate, standard error, 95% lower/upper, benchmark, gap=estimate-benchmark, covariates, support, estimator, and retained treated/control N. Figure must show all nine observational estimates with 95% intervals and benchmark as horizontal line; Okabe-Ito palette/theme constants at top of script, caption not title, zero-line if useful, 300+ dpi, exactly one PNG at figures/spec-curve.png. Table must include all nine rows, dollars sensibly rounded, benchmark/gap, intervals and sample counts. Memo around 450 words must adjudicate based strictly on computed curve and distinguish robust recovery, favorable-specification-only recovery, or absent recovery; concede conditional ignorability/unobserved confounding and common-support target changes. Constraints: set.seed before anything stochastic; self-contained Rscript recreates all outputs; no web; no package installation; no extra figures; do not edit BRIEF.md, sol-session.log, routing-log.md, or terra logs; no commits. Acceptance checks: Rscript script.R exits 0 from current directory; benchmark recomputed near 1794 but not hard-coded; 9 rows exactly; all 8 factorial cells present; figure PNG 300+ dpi and no in-plot title; memo 400-525 words and claims match numbers. Return format in the log: conclusion, evidence, changed files, residual risk, and tokens used.' < /dev/null > terra-implementation.log 2>&1
+```
+
+### 2. Terra verification — tokens used: 64,158
+
+```bash
+codex exec --model gpt-5.6-terra -c model_reasoning_effort=medium --sandbox read-only --skip-git-repo-check -C "$PWD" 'Objective: Independently audit the final LaLonde deliverables against BRIEF.md without changing any file. Inputs and authoritative paths: ./BRIEF.md, ./script.R, ./spec-table.md, ./memo.md, ./figures/spec-curve.png, and installed local R packages/data only. In scope: read all artifacts; run Rscript script.R only if read-only sandbox permits the script output writes to existing paths, otherwise inspect and run non-writing R checks; independently recompute the experimental benchmark and naive difference; verify the full 2 covariate x 2 support x 2 estimator grid plus naive row; check ATT matching with replacement, trimming definition/counts, subclassification weighting, interval methods and absence of ordinary NN bootstrap; check table arithmetic and memo claims; inspect PNG dimensions/DPI, exactly-one-figure condition, benchmark and zero reference lines, no in-plot title, and Okabe-Ito colors. Out of scope: editing, package installation, web access, invoking any other skill/advisor/subagent, committing, or accessing files outside this current directory. Constraints and invariants: treat artifacts as final; do not write or revise them; report exact numeric evidence and distinguish errors from limitations. Write ownership: none; only this command shell writes terra-verification.log. Expected artifact: a concise audit in stdout captured to terra-verification.log. Acceptance checks: state PASS or FAIL for each requested deliverable and overall; identify any unsupported inference or arithmetic mismatch; end with residual risk and the exact tokens-used count exposed by the session. Return format: conclusion, checks with evidence, changed files (must be none), residual risk, tokens used.' < /dev/null > terra-verification.log 2>&1
+```
+
+The CLI appended the numeric token counts shown above to each `.log`, even though each worker's prose said the count was not exposed to its model.
+
+## What Sol reasoned directly
+
+The lead fixed the estimand as the NSW-treated ATT, selected the complete eight-cell grid, defined common support from full-composite fitted-score ranges, and kept fitted scores fixed across support variants. It chose a control-reuse CR1 approximation conditional on fitted scores for 1-NN matching (with a cluster-count t critical value), a treated-weighted Neyman fixed-strata variance for subclassification, and a Welch interval for the naive contrast. The lead also adjudicated the evidence as favorable-specification-only recovery: earnings-inclusive 1-NN estimates approach the experimental benchmark, but demographics-only and some subclassification results do not.
+
+## Friction
+
+The implementation worker's first internal `apply_patch` attempt had an invalid hunk and was retried successfully. Its attempted independent advisor review was blocked by the documented nested-process sandbox restriction. The lead found and corrected an overgeneral statement that trimming changed the realized treated target; all 185 treated units were retained here. The read-only verifier could not run R because its sandbox could not create an R temporary file, but it completed a static audit and correctly flagged that the default macOS PNG device omitted physical-resolution metadata. Within the single integration revision cycle, the lead switched rendering to `ragg::agg_png`; `sips` and ImageMagick then verified 320×320 dpi and a `pHYs` density chunk. The lead also softened one aggregate-to-unit-level inference in the memo. No web access, package installation, commit, push, or write outside the current leaf was performed.
+
+[SOL LEAD TOKENS: ____]  + Terra one-shots: 184,615  = <184,615 + SOL LEAD TOKENS>
